(10217, 'TT', '2 PAGE', 'TTT', 'Hey**yy** \\r\\n- 66666\\r\\n- 6666\\r\\n### yyyy\\r\\n[https://apps.abacus.ai/chatllm/](https://example.com)\\r\\n1. \\r\\n1. \\r\\n| Header 1 | Header 2 | Header 3 |\\r\\n| -------- | -------- | -------- |\\r\\n| Cell 1   | Cell 2   | Cell 3   |\\r\\n| Cell 4   | Cell 5   | Cell 6   |1. iii\\r\\n1. ]]]]', '', NULL, 'Sue', 'poultrysue@gmail.com', '2025-05-20 17:53:00', 375, '2.00', 'Completed', '2025-05-19 21:53:57', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'WhatsApp Image 2024-02-06 at 01.32.18.jpeg,WhatsApp Image 2023-10-31 at 18.09.27.jpeg', NULL, '2025-05-22 07:56:49', '2025-05-22 07:56:49', '2025-05-24 07:14:07', '2025-05-24 11:14:07', 0),
(10218, 'TT', '2 PAGE', 'TTT', '_Climate Change: A Global Crisis_\\\\r\\\\nClimate change represents one of the most pressing challenges of the 21st century. Defined as long-term alterations in temperature, precipitation, wind patterns, and other elements of the Earth\\\\\\\'s [climate ](https://chatgpt.com/)system, _climate change_ is largely driven by human activities. \\\\r\\\\n- The overwhelming scientific - consensus indicates that greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from - burning fossil fuels, deforestation, and industrial processes have caused a rapid increase in global temperatures. This explores the causes, impacts, and potential solutions to this global crisis.', '', NULL, 'Sue', 'poultrysue@gmail.com', '2025-05-21 18:05:00', 375, '3.00', 'Submitted', '2025-05-19 22:05:47', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'taskfiles/submissions/1748267182_CRM Activity.docx', 'https://monkbrian.sfo3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/taskfiles/submissions/1748267182_CRM Activity.docx', '2025-05-26 16:46:55', NULL, NULL, '2025-05-26 13:46:55', 0),
(10219, 'tt', 'test', 'tt', '<p style=\\\"text-align: left; padding-left: 40px;\\\">The Commerce Clause and Environmental Injustice: How Legal Frameworks Perpetuate Toxic Exposure in Minority Communities<br>1. Environmental justice issues permeate American society, affecting marginalized communities at disproportionate rates.</p>\\r\\n<p>2. One particularly insidious issue is how the legal and regulatory framework in the United States, specifically the Commerce Clause of the Constitution, has been weaponized to force minority communities to accept hazardous waste facilities. This paper examines how the Commerce Clause contributes to environmental injustice, who bears the consequences of this injustice, the structural causes behind it, and potential remedies that could address these inequities.<br><strong>The Nature and Manifestation of Environmental Injustice</strong><br>The Commerce Clause has been one of the most effective weapons wielded by waste management companies to force communities to accept hazardous waste or prevent jurisdictions from developing stricter waste <em>regulations </em>than federal standards (Taylor, 2014). According to Taylor (2014), courts have consistently ruled that local legislation cannot hinder the movement of &ldquo;articles of commerce&rdquo; (including toxic waste) across state lines. When communities attempt to block hazardous waste from being processed within their boundaries, courts strike down these ordinances, arguing that &ldquo;the safe disposal of hazardous wastes is a national interest&rdquo; that supersedes local concerns about health and environmental risks (Taylor, 2014, p. 99).</p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', NULL, 'Sue', 'poultrysue@gmail.com', '2025-05-22 10:14:00', 375, '2.00', 'In Progress', '2025-05-21 14:14:37', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-05-21 14:14:37', 0),
(10220, 'tt', 'test', 'tt', '<h3>3. <strong>Summary of what happens</strong></h3><ol><li data-list=\\\"bullet\\\"><span class=\\\"ql-ui\\\" contenteditable=\\\"false\\\"></span>User fills out the form and uses the Quill editor.</li><li data-list=\\\"bullet\\\"><span class=\\\"ql-ui\\\" contenteditable=\\\"false\\\"></span>When the form is submitted, the Quill editor’s HTML is copied into the hidden input.</li><li data-list=\\\"bullet\\\"><span class=\\\"ql-ui\\\" contenteditable=\\\"false\\\"></span>The hidden input is submitted with the rest of the form.</li><li data-list=\\\"bullet\\\"><span class=\\\"ql-ui\\\" contenteditable=\\\"false\\\"></span>Your PHP code saves the HTML content in the database.</li></ol><p><br></p>', '', NULL, 'Sue', 'poultrysue@gmail.com', '2025-05-22 13:16:00', 375, '2.00', 'In Progress', '2025-05-21 17:16:25', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', NULL, '2025-05-21 13:30:16', NULL, NULL, '2025-05-21 17:30:16', 0);
INSERT INTO `tbltasks` (`id`, `account`, `topic`, `subject`, `description`, `task_files`, `file_urls`, `writer`, `email`, `due_date`, `cpp`, `pages`, `status`, `create_date`, `is_paid`, `is_confirmed`, `is_archived`, `is_favorite`, `is_duplicate`, `submitted_files`, `submitted_file_urls`, `submitted_on`, `completed_on`, `paid_on`, `update_date`, `is_deleted`) VALUES
(10221, 'tt', 'test', 'tt', '<p>Climate change also intensifies extreme weather events, including hurricanes, droughts, and wildfires. For instance, hurricanes fueled by warmer ocean waters have become more powerful and destructive, as evidenced by recent storms in the Atlantic. Prolonged droughts in regions like Sub-Saharan Africa threaten food security, while wildfires in Australia and California highlight the dangers posed to both ecosystems and human settlements.</p><p>Biodiversity is another casualty of climate change. Rising <a href=\\\"http://localhost/falcon.sub/sudo/create-task\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">temperatures </a>and shifting habitats disrupt ecosystems, leading to species migration, extinction, and reduced biodiversity. Coral reefs, which support marine life and protect coastlines, are under threat from ocean warming and acidification.<img src=\\\"data:image/jpeg;base64,', '', NULL, 'Sue', 'poultrysue@gmail.com', '2025-05-22 13:31:00', 375, '3.00', 'In Progress', '2025-05-21 17:31:43', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-05-21 17:31:43', 0);
